ACT:
     Cycle-Rickshaw Bye-Law 1960-Bye-Law 3(1) Cycle Rickshaw
Drivers-Court Framing Scheme.



HEADNOTE:
     The Delhi	Municipal Corporation Which framed the Cycle
Rickshaw Bye  Law of  1960 under  section 481  of the  Delhi
Municipal Corporation Act, 1957 amended Bye-law 3 in 1976 to
provide that  'no person  shall keep or ply for hire a cycle
rickshaw in Delhi unless he himself is the owner thereof and
holds a licence granted in that behalf'.
     In writ petitions challenging the provision:
